Globalization gives large transnational corporations power over agriculture, generating an exodus of farmers and making it impossible to end hunger in the World because production ends up in the hands of only those who can afford it. The market cannot end hunger because it is not made to satisfy needs, and does not balance supply and need, but rather supply and demand.
